Class.Name: NSDocument
Class.Description: An abstract class that defines the interface for macOS documents.

InstanceMethods.Name: init
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes and returns an empty document object.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithContentsOfURL:ofType:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a document located by a URL of a specified type.

InstanceMethods.Name: initForURL:withContentsOfURL:ofType:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a document with the specified contents, and places the resulting document's file at the designated location.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithType:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a document of a specified type.

InstanceMethods.Name: readFromURL:ofType:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets the contents of this document by reading from a file or file package, of a specified type, located by a URL.

InstanceMethods.Name: readFromFileWrapper:ofType:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets the contents of this document by reading from a file wrapper of a specified type.

InstanceMethods.Name: readFromData:ofType:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets the contents of this document by reading from data of a specified type.

InstanceMethods.Name: canAsynchronouslyWriteToURL:ofType:forSaveOperation:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns whether the receiver can concurrently write to a file or file package located by a URL, that is formatted for a specific type, for a specific kind of save operation.

InstanceMethods.Name: unblockUserInteraction
InstanceMethods.Description: Unblocks the main thread during asynchronous saving.

InstanceMethods.Name: writeToURL:ofType:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Writes the contents of the document to a file or file package located by a URL, that is formatted to a specified type.

InstanceMethods.Name: writeSafelyToURL:ofType:forSaveOperation:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Writes the contents of the document to a file or file package located by a URL.

InstanceMethods.Name: fileWrapperOfType:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates and returns a file wrapper that contains the contents of the document, formatted to the specified type.

InstanceMethods.Name: dataOfType:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates and returns a data object that contains the contents of the document, formatted to a specified type.

InstanceMethods.Name: writeToURL:ofType:forSaveOperation:originalContentsURL:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Writes the contents of the document to a file or file package located by a URL.

InstanceMethods.Name: saveToURL:ofType:forSaveOperation:delegate:didSaveSelector:contextInfo:
InstanceMethods.Description: Saves the contents of the document to a file or file package located by a URL, that is formatted to a specified type, for a particular kind of save operation.

InstanceMethods.Name: saveToURL:ofType:forSaveOperation:completionHandler:
InstanceMethods.Description: Saves the contents of the document to a file or file package located by a URL, that is formatted to a specified type, for a particular kind of save operation, and invokes the passed-in completion handler.

InstanceMethods.Name: fileAttributesToWriteToURL:ofType:forSaveOperation:originalContentsURL:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the attributes to write to the file or file package at the specified URL, and targeting the specified type of save operation.

InstanceMethods.Name: writableTypesForSaveOperation:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the names of the types to which this document can be saved for a specified kind of save operation.

InstanceMethods.Name: fileNameExtensionForType:saveOperation:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a filename extension that can be appended to a base filename, for a specified file type and kind of save operation.

InstanceMethods.Name: makeWindowControllers
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates the window controller objects that the document uses to display its content.

InstanceMethods.Name: addWindowController:
InstanceMethods.Description: Adds the specified window controller to the current document.

InstanceMethods.Name: removeWindowController:
InstanceMethods.Description: Removes the specified window controller from the receiver’s array of window controllers.

InstanceMethods.Name: windowControllerDidLoadNib:
InstanceMethods.Description: Called after one of the document's window controllers loads its nib file.

InstanceMethods.Name: windowControllerWillLoadNib:
InstanceMethods.Description: Called before one of the document's window controllers loads its nib file.

InstanceMethods.Name: shouldCloseWindowController:delegate:shouldCloseSelector:contextInfo:
InstanceMethods.Description: Determines whether the system should close the document and its associated window.

InstanceMethods.Name: showWindows
InstanceMethods.Description: Displays all of the document’s windows, bringing them to the front and making them main or key as necessary.

InstanceMethods.Name: setWindow:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets the window outlet of this document to the specified value.

InstanceMethods.Name: setDisplayName:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets the name of this document for presentation to the user.

InstanceMethods.Name: defaultDraftName
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the default draft name for the document subclass.

InstanceMethods.Name: encodeRestorableStateWithCoder:backgroundQueue:
InstanceMethods.Description: Saves the interface-related state of the document.

InstanceMethods.Name: checkAutosavingSafetyAndReturnError:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether it is safe to autosave document changes.

InstanceMethods.Name: scheduleAutosaving
InstanceMethods.Description: Schedules periodic autosaving for the purpose of crash protection.

InstanceMethods.Name: autosaveDocumentWithDelegate:didAutosaveSelector:contextInfo:
InstanceMethods.Description: Autosaves the document’s contents to an appropriate location in the file system.

InstanceMethods.Name: autosaveWithImplicitCancellability:completionHandler:
InstanceMethods.Description: Autosaves the document’s contents to an appropriate file-system location, as needed.

InstanceMethods.Name: browseDocumentVersions:
InstanceMethods.Description: Opens the Versions browser in the document’s main window.

InstanceMethods.Name: stopBrowsingVersionsWithCompletionHandler:
InstanceMethods.Description: Dismiss the Versions browser for the current document.

InstanceMethods.Name: moveDocumentToUbiquityContainer:
InstanceMethods.Description: Moves the document to the user’s iCloud storage.

InstanceMethods.Name: updateChangeCountWithToken:forSaveOperation:
InstanceMethods.Description: Updates the document's change count settings after a successful save operation.

InstanceMethods.Name: updateChangeCount:
InstanceMethods.Description: Updates the receiver’s change count according to the given change type.

InstanceMethods.Name: changeCountTokenForSaveOperation:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an object that encapsulates the current record of document changes at the beginning of a save operation.

InstanceMethods.Name: encodeRestorableStateWithCoder:
InstanceMethods.Description: Saves the interface-related state of the document.

InstanceMethods.Name: restoreStateWithCoder:
InstanceMethods.Description: Restores the interface-related state of the document.

InstanceMethods.Name: invalidateRestorableState
InstanceMethods.Description: Marks the document’s interface-related state as dirty.

InstanceMethods.Name: restoreDocumentWindowWithIdentifier:state:completionHandler:
InstanceMethods.Description: Restores a window that was associated with a document, after that document is reopened.

InstanceMethods.Name: runModalSavePanelForSaveOperation:delegate:didSaveSelector:contextInfo:
InstanceMethods.Description: Presents a modal Save panel to the user, then tries to save the document if the user approves the operation.

InstanceMethods.Name: prepareSavePanel:
InstanceMethods.Description: Tells the document to customize the specified Save panel.

InstanceMethods.Name: updateUserActivityState:
InstanceMethods.Description: Updates the state of the given user activity.

InstanceMethods.Name: validateUserInterfaceItem:
InstanceMethods.Description: Validates the specified user interface item that the receiver manages.

InstanceMethods.Name: performSynchronousFileAccessUsingBlock:
InstanceMethods.Description: Waits for any scheduled file access to complete, then invokes the passed-in block.

InstanceMethods.Name: performAsynchronousFileAccessUsingBlock:
InstanceMethods.Description: Waits for any scheduled file access to complete but without blocking the main thread, then invokes the passed-in block.

InstanceMethods.Name: performActivityWithSynchronousWaiting:usingBlock:
InstanceMethods.Description: Waits for any work scheduled by previous invocations of this method to complete, then invokes the passed-in block.

InstanceMethods.Name: continueActivityUsingBlock:
InstanceMethods.Description: Continues to perform the task for a user activity object using a different block.

InstanceMethods.Name: continueAsynchronousWorkOnMainThreadUsingBlock:
InstanceMethods.Description: Invokes the passed-in block on the main thread.

InstanceMethods.Name: printDocument:
InstanceMethods.Description: Prints the receiver in response to the user choosing the Print menu command.

InstanceMethods.Name: runPageLayout:
InstanceMethods.Description: The action method invoked in the receiver as first responder when the user chooses the Page Setup menu command.

InstanceMethods.Name: revertDocumentToSaved:
InstanceMethods.Description: The action of the File menu item Revert in a document-based app.

InstanceMethods.Name: saveDocument:
InstanceMethods.Description: The action method invoked in the receiver as first responder when the user chooses the Save menu command.

InstanceMethods.Name: saveDocumentAs:
InstanceMethods.Description: The action method invoked in the receiver as first responder when the user chooses the Save As menu command.

InstanceMethods.Name: saveDocumentTo:
InstanceMethods.Description: The action method invoked in the receiver as first responder when the user chooses the Save To menu command.

InstanceMethods.Name: saveDocumentWithDelegate:didSaveSelector:contextInfo:
InstanceMethods.Description: Saves the document and delivers the results to the provided delegate object.

InstanceMethods.Name: canCloseDocumentWithDelegate:shouldCloseSelector:contextInfo:
InstanceMethods.Description: Determines whether to close the document, prompting the user as needed to choose a course of action.

InstanceMethods.Name: close
InstanceMethods.Description: Closes all of the document's windows and removes the document from its document controller.

InstanceMethods.Name: revertToContentsOfURL:ofType:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Discards all unsaved document modifications and replaces the document’s contents by reading a file or file package located by a URL of a specified type.

InstanceMethods.Name: duplicateAndReturnError:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates a new document whose contents are the same as the receiver and returns an error object if unsuccessful.

InstanceMethods.Name: duplicateDocument:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates a copy of the receiving document in response to the user choosing Duplicate from the File menu.

InstanceMethods.Name: duplicateDocumentWithDelegate:didDuplicateSelector:contextInfo:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates a new document whose contents are the same as the current document.

InstanceMethods.Name: renameDocument:
InstanceMethods.Description: Renames the current document in response to the user choosing the Rename menu item.

InstanceMethods.Name: moveDocument:
InstanceMethods.Description: Moves the document to a new location in response to the user choosing the Move To… menu item.

InstanceMethods.Name: moveDocumentWithCompletionHandler:
InstanceMethods.Description: Moves the document to a user-selected location.

InstanceMethods.Name: moveToURL:completionHandler:
InstanceMethods.Description: Moves the document’s file to the given URL.

InstanceMethods.Name: lockDocument:
InstanceMethods.Description: Locks the document in response to the user choosing the Lock menu item.

InstanceMethods.Name: unlockDocument:
InstanceMethods.Description: Unlocks the document in response to the user choosing the Unlock menu item.

InstanceMethods.Name: lockDocumentWithCompletionHandler:
InstanceMethods.Description: Prevents the user from making further changes to the document.

InstanceMethods.Name: lockWithCompletionHandler:
InstanceMethods.Description: Prevents the user from making changes to the document's file.

InstanceMethods.Name: unlockDocumentWithCompletionHandler:
InstanceMethods.Description: Allows the user to make modifications to the document.

InstanceMethods.Name: unlockWithCompletionHandler:
InstanceMethods.Description: Allows the user to make modifications to the document's file.

InstanceMethods.Name: preparePageLayout:
InstanceMethods.Description: Adds document-specific content to the Page Layout panel.

InstanceMethods.Name: runModalPageLayoutWithPrintInfo:delegate:didRunSelector:contextInfo:
InstanceMethods.Description: Runs the modal page layout panel with the receiver’s printing information object.

InstanceMethods.Name: runModalPrintOperation:delegate:didRunSelector:contextInfo:
InstanceMethods.Description: Runs the specified print operation modally.

InstanceMethods.Name: shouldChangePrintInfo:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether the document allows changes to the default printing information.

InstanceMethods.Name: printDocumentWithSettings:showPrintPanel:delegate:didPrintSelector:contextInfo:
InstanceMethods.Description: Prints the document's contents, optionally displaying a print panel to the user.

InstanceMethods.Name: printOperationWithSettings:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates and returns a print operation for the document's contents.

InstanceMethods.Name: saveDocumentToPDF:
InstanceMethods.Description: Exports a PDF representation of the document’s current contents.

InstanceMethods.Name: prepareSharingServicePicker:
InstanceMethods.Description: Perform any custom setup associated with a sharing service picker.

InstanceMethods.Name: shareDocumentWithSharingService:completionHandler:
InstanceMethods.Description: Share the document's file using the specified sharing service.

InstanceMethods.Name: handleCloseScriptCommand:
InstanceMethods.Description: Handles the Close AppleScript command by attempting to close the document.

InstanceMethods.Name: handlePrintScriptCommand:
InstanceMethods.Description: Handles the Print AppleScript command by attempting to print the document.

InstanceMethods.Name: handleSaveScriptCommand:
InstanceMethods.Description: Handles the Save AppleScript command by attempting to save the document.

InstanceMethods.Name: presentError:modalForWindow:delegate:didPresentSelector:contextInfo:
InstanceMethods.Description: Presents an error alert to the user as a modal panel.

InstanceMethods.Name: presentError:
InstanceMethods.Description: Presents an error alert to the user as a modal panel.

InstanceMethods.Name: willPresentError:
InstanceMethods.Description: Called when the receiver is about to present an error.

InstanceMethods.Name: willNotPresentError:
InstanceMethods.Description: Confirms that the error object is not to be presented to the user and the error cannot be recovered from, so cleanup can be done.

InstanceProperties.Name: fileURL
InstanceProperties.Description: The location of the document’s on-disk representation.

InstanceProperties.Name: entireFileLoaded
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value that indicates whether the document’s file is completely loaded into memory.

InstanceProperties.Name: fileModificationDate
InstanceProperties.Description: The last-known modification date of the document’s on-disk representation.

InstanceProperties.Name: keepBackupFile
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value that indicates whether the document archives previously saved versions of the document.

InstanceProperties.Name: draft
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value that indicates whether the document is a draft that the user has not yet saved.

InstanceProperties.Name: fileType
InstanceProperties.Description: The name of the document type, as specified in the app’s information property-list file.

InstanceProperties.Name: documentEdited
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value that indicates whether the document has unsaved changes.

InstanceProperties.Name: inViewingMode
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value that indicates whether the document is in read-only mode.

InstanceProperties.Name: windowControllers
InstanceProperties.Description: The document’s current window controllers.

InstanceProperties.Name: windowNibName
InstanceProperties.Description: The name of the document’s sole nib file.

InstanceProperties.Name: windowForSheet
InstanceProperties.Description: Returns the document window to use as the parent of a document-modal sheet.

InstanceProperties.Name: displayName
InstanceProperties.Description: The name of the document as displayed in the title bars of the document’s windows and in alert dialogs related to the document.

InstanceProperties.Name: autosavedContentsFileURL
InstanceProperties.Description: The location of the most recently autosaved document contents.

InstanceProperties.Name: autosavingFileType
InstanceProperties.Description: Returns the document type to use for an autosave operation.

InstanceProperties.Name: autosavingIsImplicitlyCancellable
InstanceProperties.Description: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether you can cancel an in-progress autosave operation.

InstanceProperties.Name: hasUnautosavedChanges
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value that indicates whether the document has changes that have not been autosaved.

InstanceProperties.Name: backupFileURL
InstanceProperties.Description: The URL for the document’s backup file that was created during an autosave operation.

InstanceProperties.Name: browsingVersions
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value that indicates whether the document is currently displaying the Versions browser.

InstanceProperties.Name: undoManager
InstanceProperties.Description: The object that the document uses to support undo/redo operations.

InstanceProperties.Name: hasUndoManager
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value that indicates whether the document owns an undo manager object.

InstanceProperties.Name: shouldRunSavePanelWithAccessoryView
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value that indicates whether the document’s Save panel displays a list of supported writable document types.

InstanceProperties.Name: fileTypeFromLastRunSavePanel
InstanceProperties.Description: The file type that was last selected in the Save panel.

InstanceProperties.Name: fileNameExtensionWasHiddenInLastRunSavePanel
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value that indicates whether the user chose to hide the document's filename extension.

InstanceProperties.Name: userActivity
InstanceProperties.Description: An object that encapsulates a user activity supported by this document.

InstanceProperties.Name: locked
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value that indicates whether or not the file can be written to.

InstanceProperties.Name: printInfo
InstanceProperties.Description: The printing information associated with the document.

InstanceProperties.Name: PDFPrintOperation
InstanceProperties.Description: A print operation you can use to create a PDF representation of the document’s current contents.

InstanceProperties.Name: allowsDocumentSharing
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value that indicates whether the document is shareable from the standard Share menu.

InstanceProperties.Name: objectSpecifier
InstanceProperties.Description: Returns the object specifier that represents the document.

InstanceProperties.Name: lastComponentOfFileName
InstanceProperties.Description: The name of the document seen by the user in AppleScript.

TypeMethods.Name: canConcurrentlyReadDocumentsOfType:
TypeMethods.Description: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether the receiver reads multiple documents of the given type concurrently.

TypeMethods.Name: isNativeType:
TypeMethods.Description: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether the document can read and write the data natively.

TypeMethods.Name: allowedClassesForRestorableStateKeyPath:
TypeMethods.Description: Returns the classes that support secure coding.

TypeProperties.Name: readableTypes
TypeProperties.Description: Returns the types of data the receiver can read natively and any types filterable to that native type.

TypeProperties.Name: writableTypes
TypeProperties.Description: Returns the types of data the receiver can write natively and any types filterable to that native type.

TypeProperties.Name: autosavesInPlace
TypeProperties.Description: Returns whether the receiver supports autosaving in place.

TypeProperties.Name: autosavesDrafts
TypeProperties.Description: A Boolean value that indicates whether the document subclass supports autosaving of drafts.

TypeProperties.Name: preservesVersions
TypeProperties.Description: Returns whether the document subclass supports version management.

TypeProperties.Name: usesUbiquitousStorage
TypeProperties.Description: Returns whether the document object stores its contents in the user's iCloud document storage.

TypeProperties.Name: restorableStateKeyPaths
TypeProperties.Description: Returns an array of key paths that represent the restorable attributes of the document.
